==English==
===Pronunciation===
*wīt, {{IPA|/waɪt/}}, /<tt>waIt</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[white]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-aɪt|Rhymes: -aɪt]]

===Etymology 1===
Old English [[wiht]], from Germanic ''*wixtiz''.  Cognate with Dutch [[wicht]], German [[Wicht]], Swedish [[vätte]].

====Noun====
'''wight'''

#(''archaic or obsolete'') A [[living]] [[creature]], especially [[human]].

===Etymology 2===
From Old Norse [[vígt]], neuter of [[vígr]] ‘skilled in fighting, of age’, cognate with Old English [[wig#Old English|wīġ]].

====Adjective====
'''wight'''

#(''archaic except in dialects'') [[brave]], [[valourous]], [[strong]]

